<paragraph id="8BC07D1FFF83FFE36384FB09FB39F995" blockId="2.[136,1452,1274,1805]" pageId="2" pageNumber="291">
<emphasis id="B90BA10DFF83FFE36384FB09FF69FAFC" bold="true" box="[136,203,1274,1300]" pageId="2" pageNumber="291">Notes</emphasis>
:― 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEE00EEFF83FFE363E0FB08FE61FAFD" author="Freyn, J." box="[236,451,1274,1301]" pageId="2" pageNumber="291" pagination="1058 - 1068" refId="ref3495" refString="Freyn, J. (1903) Plantae ex Asia Media. Bulletin de l'Herbier Boissier ser. 2, 3: 1058 - 1068." type="journal article" year="1903">Freyn (1903:1062)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName id="4C7F069CFF83FFE36133FB08FC34FAFC" authorityName="Freyn (1903:" authorityYear="1062" box="[575,918,1274,1301]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Tamaricaceae" genus="Tamarix" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="2" pageNumber="291" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="variety" species="karakalensis" variety="myriantha">
<emphasis id="B90BA10DFF83FFE36133FB08FD4BFAFC" box="[575,745,1274,1300]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="291">T. karakalensis</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="B90BA10DFF83FFE3602FFB09FC34FAFC" box="[803,918,1274,1300]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="291">myriantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on the 
<emphasis id="B90BA10DFF83FFE36739FB08FB62FAFC" box="[1077,1216,1274,1301]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="291">Sintenis 467</emphasis>
collection, though it appears referenced to 
<emphasis id="B90BA10DFF83FFE3628FFAECFDACFAD0" box="[387,526,1310,1337]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="291">Sintenis 477</emphasis>
. That seems to be a typing mistake, as the number 467 occurs in the labels of all 
<typeStatus id="54C4C3BDFF83FFE36384FAB0FF48FAB5" box="[136,234,1347,1373]" pageId="2" pageNumber="291">syntypes</typeStatus>
found at G, LD, P, PR and W, even in the voucher that was personally examined by Freyn (LD-1666462). We have not found any sheet numbered 
<emphasis id="B90BA10DFF83FFE3615DFA94FD7EFA68" box="[593,732,1382,1409]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="291">Sintenis 477</emphasis>
from the “Iter transcaspico persicum 1900–1901” in any of the studied herbaria. As in the previous case, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEE00EEFF83FFE36164FA78FC8EFA4D" author="Baum, B." box="[616,812,1418,1445]" pageId="2" pageNumber="291" refId="ref3462" refString="Baum, B. (1966) Monographic Revision of the genus Tamarix. Final research report for the USDA. Department of Botany, Hebrew University, Jerusalem, 193 pp." type="book" year="1966">Baum (1966: 62)</bibRefCitation>
said that the 
<typeStatus id="54C4C3BDFF83FFE360C5FA79FB89FA4C" box="[969,1067,1418,1444]" pageId="2" pageNumber="291">holotype</typeStatus>
of this taxon to be at G, and this selection must prevail (Art. 7.9, and 7.10 of the ICN). The use of “ 
<typeStatus id="54C4C3BDFF83FFE3606CFA5DFC65FA20" box="[864,967,1454,1480]" pageId="2" pageNumber="291">holotype</typeStatus>
” has to be corrected to “ 
<typeStatus id="54C4C3BDFF83FFE367DDFA5DFA9FFA20" box="[1233,1341,1454,1480]" pageId="2" pageNumber="291">lectotype</typeStatus>
” (Art. 9.9 of the ICN), and the selection of 
<typeStatus id="54C4C3BDFF83FFE362FAFA21FDFFFA04" box="[502,605,1490,1516]" pageId="2" pageNumber="291">lectotype</typeStatus>
has to be narrowed (Art. 9.17 Ex. 12 of the ICN), as more than one voucher is kept at G, and none of them is clearly marked as 
<typeStatus id="54C4C3BDFF83FFE361DCFA05FC94F9F8" box="[720,822,1526,1552]" pageId="2" pageNumber="291">holotype</typeStatus>
. The voucher G-00359278 is here selected as 
<typeStatus id="54C4C3BDFF83FFE36632FA05FA0AF9F8" box="[1342,1448,1526,1552]" pageId="2" pageNumber="291">lectotype</typeStatus>
, as it is a complete and well preserved specimen. Any other copy of the 
<emphasis id="B90BA10DFF83FFE360A0F9E8FB94F9DC" box="[940,1078,1562,1589]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="291">Sintenis 467</emphasis>
collection must be considered as isolectotype. According to our observations, the morphological variability of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C7F069CFF83FFE36704F9CCFB08F9B0" authorityName="Freyn (1903:" authorityYear="1062" box="[1032,1194,1598,1625]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Tamaricaceae" genus="Tamarix" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="2" pageNumber="291" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="variety" species="karakalensis" variety="myriantha">
var. 
<emphasis id="B90BA10DFF83FFE3673BF9CDFB08F9B0" box="[1079,1194,1598,1624]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="291">myriantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is completely included in that of the nominal variety. We agree with 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEE00EEFF83FFE3618EF990FCE1F994" author="Baum, B." box="[642,835,1634,1661]" pageId="2" pageNumber="291" refId="ref3462" refString="Baum, B. (1966) Monographic Revision of the genus Tamarix. Final research report for the USDA. Department of Botany, Hebrew University, Jerusalem, 193 pp." type="book" year="1966">Baum (1966: 33)</bibRefCitation>
, who synonymized the names.
</paragraph>
